---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebSite",
  "name": "Sydney Anxiety Psychology",
  "description": "Directory helping people in Sydney find AHPRA-registered telehealth psychologists who specialise in anxiety.",
  "url": "https://sydneyanxietypsychology.com.au/",
  "potentialAction": {
    "@type": "SearchAction",
    "target": "https://sydneyanxietypsychology.com.au/connect/",
    "query-input": "required name=search_term_string"
  }
};

const itemListSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "ItemList",
  "name": "How to Access a Telehealth Psychologist for Anxiety in Sydney",
  "itemListElement": [
    {
      "@type": "ListItem",
      "position": 1,
      "name": "See your GP for a Mental Health Treatment Plan (optional but recommended for Medicare rebates)"
    },
    {
      "@type": "ListItem",
      "position": 2,
      "name": "Find an AHPRA-registered psychologist who specialises in anxiety and offers telehealth"
    },
    {
      "@type": "ListItem",
      "position": 3,
      "name": "Book an initial appointment — telehealth sessions take place via video call from home"
    },
    {
      "@type": "ListItem",
      "position": 4,
      "name": "Claim your Medicare rebate after each session (up to 10 sessions per calendar year)"
    }
  ]
};
---
<Base
  title="Telehealth Psychologist for Anxiety Sydney | Medicare Rebates | Finder"
  description="Find an AHPRA-registered telehealth psychologist specialising in anxiety in Sydney. Clear fees, Medicare rebate information, and no waitlist surprises."
  schema={[schema, itemListSchema]}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hero__label">Telehealth Psychologist Directory — Sydney</p>
      <h1 class="hero__headline">Find a Telehealth Psychologist for Anxiety in Sydney</h1>
      <p class="hero__subheadline">
        A directory of AHPRA-registered psychologists in Sydney offering telehealth appointments for anxiety. Clear fees, Medicare information, and no jargon — so you can focus on finding the right person.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__cta-group">
        <a href="/connect/" class="btn btn--primary plausible-event-name=Hero+CTA+Click">
          Find a Psychologist
        </a>
        <a href="/guides/cost-telehealth-psychologist-australia/" class="btn btn--secondary">
          What does it cost?
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="trust-strip">
        <div class="trust-strip__item">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z"/><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-4"/></svg>
          AHPRA-registered psychologists
        </div>
        <div class="trust-strip__item">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M16 8h-6a2 2 0 1 0 0 4h4a2 2 0 1 1 0 4H8"/><path d="M12 18V6"/></svg>
          Medicare rebates available
        </div>
        <div class="trust-strip__item">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m22 8-6 4 6 4V8Z"/><rect width="14" height="12" x="2" y="6" rx="2" ry="2"/></svg>
          Sydney-wide telehealth
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="info-box">
        <p><strong>Medicare rebates apply to telehealth psychology.</strong> With a Mental Health Treatment Plan from your GP, you can claim a Medicare rebate on telehealth psychology sessions — the same rebate as an in-person appointment. For a registered psychologist, the rebate is <strong>$98.95 per session</strong> (from 1 July 2025). <a href="/guides/cost-telehealth-psychologist-australia/">Full cost breakdown &rarr;</a></p>
      </div>

      <h2>What You Can Expect</h2>
      <p>If you're looking for support with anxiety — whether that's generalised anxiety, panic attacks, social anxiety, health anxiety, or something you're still working out — here's what the process typically looks like:</p>

      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <div>
            <strong>Get a Mental Health Treatment Plan from your GP (recommended)</strong>
            <p>A Mental Health Treatment Plan (MHTP) from your GP gives you access to Medicare rebates on psychology sessions. You don't need one to see a psychologist — but without one, the full fee applies. Most GPs can issue an MHTP at a standard appointment. <a href="/guides/cost-telehealth-psychologist-australia/#mental-health-treatment-plan">How it works &rarr;</a></p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div>
            <strong>Find an AHPRA-registered psychologist who specialises in anxiety</strong>
            <p>Not every psychologist specialises in anxiety. This directory focuses specifically on registered psychologists in Sydney who work with anxiety — including generalised anxiety disorder, panic disorder, social anxiety, health anxiety, and OCD. All listed psychologists hold current AHPRA registration, which you can verify independently.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div>
            <strong>Book a telehealth appointment — from home, on video call</strong>
            <p>Telehealth psychology sessions take place via a secure video call from wherever you are in New South Wales. Most clients join from home. There's no travel, no waiting room, and sessions are typically 50–60 minutes. The first appointment is usually focused on understanding your situation — there's no pressure to have everything figured out before you arrive.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div>
            <strong>Claim your Medicare rebate after each session</strong>
            <p>After each session, your psychologist will issue a receipt. You claim your Medicare rebate via the Medicare app, MyGov, or at a Medicare service centre. Rebates are typically processed within a few business days. Up to 10 sessions per calendar year are covered under Better Access.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="cta-block">
        <h3>Ready to find a telehealth psychologist for anxiety?</h3>
        <p>Tell us a little about what you're looking for and we'll connect you with a suitable psychologist in Sydney. You'll hear back within 1 business day.</p>
        <a href="/connect/" class="btn--cta plausible-event-name=Mid+CTA+Click">
          Connect me with a psychologist
        </a>
        <p class="cta-block__note">Free to use. We'll ask your name, email, and suburb — nothing more.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Why Telehealth for Anxiety?</h2>
      <p>Telehealth psychology is not a lesser version of in-person therapy — it's a genuinely effective option that works particularly well for anxiety. You can attend from home, on your schedule, without the added stress of travel or waiting rooms.</p>

      <div class="pillar-grid">
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <span class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M16 8h-6a2 2 0 1 0 0 4h4a2 2 0 1 1 0 4H8"/><path d="M12 18V6"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Same Medicare rebates</h3>
          <p>Telehealth psychology sessions attract the same Medicare rebate as in-person sessions under the Better Access scheme. There's no difference in coverage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <span class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3.22 12H9.5l.5-1 2 4.5 2-7 1.5 3.5h5.27"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Effective for anxiety</h3>
          <p>Research consistently supports telehealth CBT and other evidence-based therapies for anxiety as being as effective as in-person delivery for most people.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <span class="pillar-card__icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Shorter wait times</h3>
          <p>Telehealth removes geography as a barrier. You're not limited to psychologists within driving distance, which means shorter waits and more choice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p><a href="/guides/does-online-therapy-work-for-anxiety/">Does online therapy actually work for anxiety? &rarr;</a></p>

      <h2>What Does It Cost?</h2>
      <p>The total cost depends on the psychologist's fee and whether you have a Mental Health Treatment Plan for Medicare rebates. Here's a straightforward summary:</p>

      <table class="fee-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Situation</th>
            <th>Medicare rebate</th>
            <th>Typical out-of-pocket</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Registered psychologist + MHTP in place</td>
            <td class="highlight">$98.95/session</td>
            <td>$50–$150 depending on the practitioner's fee</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>No MHTP (self-referred, no GP plan)</td>
            <td>No Medicare rebate</td>
            <td>Full fee applies: typically $150–$250/session</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Bulk-billing psychologists</td>
            <td>$98.95 covers full fee</td>
            <td>$0 — some psychologists bulk bill (limited availability)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">Rebate amount: Medicare Benefits Schedule, effective 1 July 2025. <a href="/guides/cost-telehealth-psychologist-australia/">Full cost guide &rarr;</a></p>

      <div class="faq">
        <h2>Common Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">Do I need a referral to see a psychologist online?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">You do not need a referral to see a psychologist. You can book directly. However, a referral in the form of a Mental Health Treatment Plan (MHTP) from your GP is required to access Medicare rebates. Without an MHTP, you pay the full fee. From November 2025, Medicare rebates generally require the referral to come from your usual GP or a GP at a practice where you're enrolled via MyMedicare — see your regular GP for the plan if possible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">Is telehealth as effective as seeing a psychologist in person?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">Research consistently supports telehealth psychology as effective for anxiety disorders — including CBT delivered via video call. Many people find the home environment actually reduces the anxiety associated with attending in-person. It's not the right format for everyone, but for most anxiety presentations it works well. <a href="/guides/does-online-therapy-work-for-anxiety/">More on the evidence &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">How many sessions will I need?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">This varies significantly depending on your situation, the type of anxiety, and what you're working toward. A standard evidence-based anxiety treatment (such as CBT) typically involves 8–12 sessions. Medicare covers up to 10 sessions per calendar year under Better Access, with a GP review after the first 6. Your psychologist will discuss expectations with you in the first appointment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">What kind of anxiety do the listed psychologists treat?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">The directory focuses on psychologists who work with anxiety broadly — including generalised anxiety disorder (GAD), panic disorder, social anxiety, health anxiety, agoraphobia, and OCD. When you make contact, you can tell us which type you're dealing with and we'll match you accordingly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">What actually happens in the first session?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">The first appointment is primarily a conversation — the psychologist will ask about your situation, what you've been experiencing, and what you're hoping to get from therapy. They'll explain their approach and answer your questions. You are not committing to anything beyond that initial session. Most people find it less daunting than they expected. <a href="/guides/how-telehealth-psychology-works/">Full guide: how telehealth psychology sessions work &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__item">
          <p class="faq__q">I keep hitting waitlists — what should I do?</p>
          <p class="faq__a">This is genuinely common in Sydney. Telehealth significantly expands your options — you're not limited to psychologists within your suburb, which opens up the full pool of practitioners across NSW. Booking your GP Mental Health Treatment Plan in parallel (not after) also saves time. <a href="/guides/psychologist-waitlist-sydney/">Guide: waitlists, availability, and how to be seen sooner &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reviewer-box">
        <div>
          <span class="reviewer-box__label">Professionally reviewed by</span>
          <p class="reviewer-box__meta">Monica Ma — Registered Psychologist, AHPRA Registration No. PSY0002701499. You can <a href="https://www.ahpra.gov.au/Registration/Registers-of-Practitioners.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">verify any psychologist's registration at ahpra.gov.au</a>. Last reviewed: June 2026.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cta-block">
        <h3>Take the first step</h3>
        <p>If you're ready to connect with a telehealth psychologist who specialises in anxiety, we can help. Tell us a little about what you're looking for — you'll hear back within 1 business day.</p>
        <a href="/connect/" class="btn--cta plausible-event-name=Bottom+CTA+Click">
          Find a psychologist for anxiety
        </a>
        <p class="cta-block__note">No obligation. We only connect you — we don't provide clinical services.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
